ros uses a set of lunix system environment variables in order to work properly.
you can check these variables by typing :

~/catkin_ws$ export |grep ROS

output :
declare -x ROSLISP_PACKAGE_DIRECTORIES=""
declare -x ROS_DISTRO="indigo"
declare -x ROS_ETC_DIR="/opt/ros/indigo/etc/ros"  
declare -x ROS_MASTER_URI="http://localhost:11311" (can be accesed in any system)
declare -x ROS_PACKAGE_PATH="/opt/ros/indigo/share:/opt/ros/indigo/stacks"
declare -x ROS_ROOT="/opt/ros/indigo/share/ros"
